node.title: Spring rains cause flash flooding in central Victoria
node.alt: a road with water over it in a country town
node.description: Spring rains have lashed Bendigo, Maldon, and Avonmore overnight with flash flooding seen across the region.
node.content:
["Spring rains have lashed central Victoria overnight with flash flooding seen across the region.", "In Bendigo, 38.6 millimetres fell overnight, with 36mm in Maldon, and 22mm at Avonmore.\u00a0", "", "
Roads were covered with water in Tarnagulla.(Supplied: Chris Fulkerson)
", "Natalie Stanway, deputy controller with the Bendigo SES, said\u00a0it was busy into the night, but not as busy as last week\u00a0when they had more than 70 calls for assistance\u00a0after damaging winds.", "\"So no roofs coming off or anything like that,\" she said.", "\"Building damage was the biggest issue. There were properties where tiles had shifted, downpipes were not maintained, and water on the ground which couldn't get away quick enough threatening to enter homes.\"", "Powercor said thousands of central Victorian properties lost power last night\u00a0but has since been restored.", "", "
Scott Street in White Hills had flash flooding.(Supplied: Natalie Stanway)
", "
Farmers rejoice
", "Jordan Collin, who runs\u00a0Huntly Organics, said the rain\u00a0was scarier last week because the combination of wind and hail was more worrying, especially for growing zucchinis and cucumbers.", "\"It wasn't that bad, fortunately. Looked like the farm was underwater though,\" he said of the overnight rain.", "", "
The flash floods brought joy to backyard ducks in Bendigo.\u00a0(ABC Central Victoria: Kimberley Price)
", "Mr Collin said\u00a0it was the spring rains they were\u00a0hoping for.", "\"It's already started to dissipate. It's turned out to be a good thing,\" he said.", "\"We just turned out lucky this time. It's just given us a really good water.\"", "Farmers are now bracing for more rain on Saturday.\u00a0", "\"If we get a few sunny days gap\u00a0it'll be okay to have rain on the weekend, but hopefully not as heavy as this,\" Mr Collin said."]
